Data Visualization¶

In [221]:
pie=full_data["company"].value_counts().reset_index()
pie.columns=["company","count"]

plt.pie(pie["count"],
        colors=sns.color_palette("pastel"),
        autopct='%.0f%%',
        labels=pie["company"])

plt.title("Cars Distribution along Companies",
          size=20)

plt.show()
In [222]:
sns.barplot(data=full_data,
            x="company",
            y="price",
            palette="pastel",
            saturation=0.99)

plt.title("Companies Price Comparison",size=20)

plt.xlabel("Company", size=15)

plt.ylabel("Price", size=15)

plt.show()
In [223]:
sns.countplot(data=full_data, 
              x='company',
              saturation=0.99,
              palette = sns.color_palette("Set2"),
              order = full_data['company'].value_counts().iloc[:15].index)

plt.title("Number of cars for each Company in the Data Set",
          size=20)

plt.xlabel("Company",
           size=15)

plt.ylabel("Count",
           size=15)

plt.show()
